Haskell-mode is the package of Haskell functionality for Emacs.

* [http://haskell.github.io/haskell-mode/ Home page] 
* [https://github.com/haskell/haskell-mode Github repository]

Some helpful notes for EmacsWiki regulars:

* [http://www.haskell.org/haskellwiki/Emacs  Additional possibly-out-of-date tidbits] by users on the Haskell wiki
* [http://haskell.org/haskellwiki/Literate_programming#Multi-mode_support_in_Emacs Using mmm-mode] (from MultipleModes) so that you can write your scholarly paper while still hacking

Related modes:

* DaRcs
* HaskellMode
* FlymakeHaskell
